```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Service Client<br/>configuration_manager
    participant S as Service Server<br/>robot_controller
    participant R as Robot Hardware

    Note over C,R: Synchronous Request-Reply Pattern

    C->>S: Request: set_control_mode<br/>{mode: "velocity", max_speed: 1.5}
    activate S
    Note over S: Validate request<br/>Check mode is valid<br/>Check speed in range

    alt Valid Request
        S->>R: Apply configuration
        R-->>S: Success
        S->>C: Response: {success: true,<br/>message: "Mode changed to velocity"}
    else Invalid Request
        S->>C: Response: {success: false,<br/>message: "Invalid mode specified"}
    end
    deactivate S

    Note over C: Process response<br/>Continue operation

    Note over C,R: Another Service Call
    C->>S: Request: get_battery_status
    activate S
    S->>R: Query battery
    R-->>S: {voltage: 24.3, percentage: 78}
    S->>C: Response: {voltage: 24.3,<br/>percentage: 78, status: "OK"}
    deactivate S
```

**Figure**: Service request-reply communication pattern. The client sends a synchronous request to the server and blocks until receiving a response. This pattern is ideal for configuration changes, queries, and short-duration computations that return a result.
